Delay in loading baggage and/or cargo due to local passenger baggage · Extended loading time of passenger baggage including volume of baggage · Late loading of cargo items such as freight, mail, co-mail, etc. that were delivered/staged on-time with appropriate documentation · Inop inplane loading system

Removing or reloading of baggage or cargo due to overweight or out of balance (includes ground interrupt). Delays due to reloading or removal of cargo for Weight and Balance purposes. This includes reloading or removal of cargo while at the gate or after a ground interrupt due to failure to follow the load plan or weight restrictions resulting in the flight being overweight or out of balance.
Late delivery or staging of cargo items such as freight, mail, co-mail, etc. (non-passenger baggage). Includes incorrect and/or incomplete documentation.
Ramp holding to load connecting baggage with less than minimum connection time available.
Delays related to ramp agent’s late retrieval of properly staged gate checked baggage – reference Are You Ready (AYR) departure protocols. · Refer to scenario #6 on page three (3)
Delays due to late or improper aircraft potable water servicing. Also includes re-servicing/topping off of potable water. · Includes items not covered by delay codes SV1 – SV7.
Untimely or improper aircraft cleaning - failure to follow company policy, procedure or process.

Untimely or improper lavatory servicing - failure to follow company policy, procedure or process. Delays due to lavatory servicing include over filling of blue juice, re-servicing lavatories that were not properly serviced, and crew requested lavatory re-servicing due to odor (passenger comfort)

Delays incurred while performing at-gate engine starts with all crew and equipment in place ontime. Delays incurred while performing non-standard engine starts (i.e. air starts) provided all personnel and equipment in place at D-7 and provided the requirement was known in advance.

Delays caused by operator not following standard ground service equipment operating procedures. This includes running out of fuel, failure to charge battery powered equipment, damage or misuse of GSE equipment.

Delays due to contract ground equipment being inoperative, unavailable or failing during use. This includes where a vendor (non-company) supports and/or provides the equipment. Delay remarks should clearly identify what equipment failed. For issues with airport owned facilities use OP2
International security cabin search, cabin panel or floor removal and search, AA gate security reviews and ID checks. · Includes items not covered by delay codes SC1 – SC5.
Onboard security concerns, passenger removal, ground interrupt, and PPBM bag processing/ removal.

Includes items not covered by delay codes CG1-CG7. · Delays include failing to follow published procedures, equipment or personnel not in place, etc. · Unauthorized loading, including loading bags that have more than minimum connect time with no HCC/Tower authorized hold.
